      • com.b2international.snowowl.datastore.request.BranchRebaseRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.b2international.snowowl.core.events.Request<com.b2international.snowowl.core.domain.RepositoryContext,com.b2international.snowowl.core.merge.Merge>, java.io.Serializable

    public final class BranchRebaseRequest
extends AbstractBranchChangeRequest<com.b2international.snowowl.core.merge.Merge>
    Rebases target on source.

    The branch represented by target is not modified; instead, a new branch representing the rebased target will be created on top of source, preserving target's path. This ensures that any changes that were made to source in the meantime will be visible on the rebased target branch.

    Commits available on the previous instance of target, if present, will also be visible on the resulting Branch after a successful rebase.

    Since:
    4.6
